[[Image:Damebandy.jpg|thumb|Finland beat Norway by 12-1 in the 2004 Women's World Championship in [[Lappeenranta#Sports|Lappeenranta]]]] The '''Bandy World Championship for women 2004''' took place in [[Lappeenranta]], [[Finland]] between 18 and 22 February. It was the first [[World Championship]] in [[bandy]] for women. Five teams took part, and firstly, all teams played in a group series, where all teams played each other once. The four best teams continued to the semi-finals. All matches were 2x30 minutes, apart from the final, which was 2 x 45 minutes. Sweden became world champions, winning their six matches a total of 52-0. In the final-game Sweden defeated Russia, 7-0.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dn.se/arkiv/sport/sveriges-bandydamer-tog-historiens-forsta-vm-guld/|title=Sveriges bandydamer tog historiens första VM-guld|publisher=Dagens nyheter|language=Swedish|date=2004|accessdate=4 February 2017}}</ref>
