{{infobox music festival | music_festival_name =August Blues Festival | image =Augustibluus.logo.png | caption = | location = [[Haapsalu]], [[Estonia]] | years_active =1993-present | founders = | dates = | genre = [[blues]] | website = {{URL|www.augustibluus.ee}} }}
The '''August Blues Festival''' ({{lang-et|Augustibluus}}) is a blues music festival held in [[Haapsalu]], [[Estonia]] since 1993.<ref name=err>{{cite news|last=Soopan|first=Ivar|title=Augustibluusil esinevad žanri suurimad tähed|url=http://uudised.err.ee/?06284539|newspaper=[[Eesti Rahvusringhääling]]|accessdate=18 October 2013|date=2013-08-02}}</ref><ref name=le>{{cite web|title=Augustibluusi 20. festival tuleb tavalisest võimsam|url=http://online.le.ee/2013/08/06/20-augustibluusi-publik-oli-aegade-suurim/|newspaper=[[Lääne Elu]]|accessdate=18 October 2013|date=2013-03-29}}</ref>
The festival takes place mainly inside the walls of [[Haapsalu Castle]].<ref name=delfi>{{cite news|title=Täna algab festival Augustibluus!|url=http://publik.delfi.ee/news/muusika/tana-algab-festival-augustibluus.d?id=66531534|accessdate=18 October 2013|newspaper=[[Delfi (web portal)|Delfi]]|date=2013-08-02}}</ref> It is the biggest blues festival in the [[Baltic states]].<ref name=ap>{{cite news|last=Hiiemäe|first=Mari|title=Augustibluus õitseb täies ilus|url=http://leht.aripaev.ee/?PublicationId=452208E7-0302-40F5-BDF9-63F8F436576F&paperid=17749960-069F-4197-B7F0-693C075D0710&selectedDate=2012-08-17|accessdate=18 October 2013|newspaper=[[Äripäev]]|date=2012-08-17}}</ref>
Besides Estonian blues musicians, there have been guests from Finland, Sweden, United States of America and elsewhere.<ref name=err/> In 2017, the Italian born blues guitarist, singer and songwriter, [[Dany Franchi]], performed at the festival.<ref name="About">{{cite web|url=https://www.danyfranchi.com/about-me/|title=About Me – Dany Franchi|website=Danyfranchi.com|accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref>
