'''Riverton City''', St Andrew, Jamaica is a [[landfill]] site on the outskirts of [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]].
In March 2015 it was the site of a major fire, starting on 11 March. The poor air quality brought a halt to activities in Kingston, as businesses, schools and other services were forced to close down early.<ref>{{cite news|title=No Timeline From Authorities On Bringing Riverton Landfill Fire Under Control|url=http://jamaica-gleaner.com/article/news/20150315/no-timeline-authorities-bringing-riverton-landfill-fire-under-control|accessdate=16 March 2015|publisher=The Gleaner|date=15 March 2015}}</ref> The [[Medical Association of Jamaica]] called on the Cabinet to tackle the public health risks, saying that at least 600 people had attended public health facilities as a result of smoke inhalation.<ref>{{cite news|title=MAJ says Cabinet must implement measures to address public health risks at Riverton landfill|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/latestnews/MAJ-says-Cabinet-must-implement-measures-to-address-public-health-risks-at-Riverton-landfill|accessdate=16 March 2015|publisher=Jamaica Observer|date=16 March 2015}}</ref>
